    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/527: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-04T01:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 4, 1944—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 3—9:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>968. Embassy learns from reliable source that this morning Foreign Office
                    received a telegram from the British Embassy in Washington reporting that the
                    United States Government was now ready to begin discussions looking toward the
                    conclusion of a general civil air agreement. The message stated that the Embassy
                    had been requested in an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> from the Department
                    to suggest an agenda. This subject was discussed this afternoon in a meeting in
                    Lord Beaver-brook’s office, attended by his staff, Air Ministry, Foreign Office
                    and service officials. It is understood that these officials believe they will
                    be ready to begin discussions in 6 to 8 weeks (<hi rend="italic">id est</hi>,
                    prepare and secure approval of the agenda).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
